question:
A clinical pharmacology manuscript includes the following LaTeX snippet typesetting the Cockcroft–Gault creatinine clearance formula:

\begin{equation*}\label{eq:crcl}
  \mathrm{CrCl} = \frac{(140 + \mathrm{age}) \times \mathrm{weight}}{72 \times \mathrm{SCr}} \times 0.75
  \quad \text{(apply if female)}
\end{equation*}
...
Equation~\eqref{eq:crcl} predicts renal clearance and guides drug dosing.

Identify every error in this snippet — both typesetting and clinical — and state the correct form of each. Do not rewrite the full snippet; name each error and give its fix.
